name: Dome in Aptos · ★4.88 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Even though we live only an 8-10 minute drive to Aptos village and the beaches, as we live on 10 acres, it feels very remote and private here. It is usually very quiet at night - sometimes we can hear the ocean waves crashing on the beach. There is lots of land to hike on and explore here as well.
We have 9 people living here in a rather loose community.
host_about:
We live on 10 beautiful acres of sun, oak forest, redwood groves and gardens with a parrot, 2 cats, a small dog, 12 chickens and from 200 - 500 hummingbirds - depending on the time of year..  

I have been hosting on airbnb since July, 2009 and really love what this company has made possible. I have met so many wonderful people from around the world that I would never have met if I hadn't had this opportunity with airbnb! Some of our guests (especially the ones from Europe) have never seen a hummingbird before and here they get to see them up close - just a few feet from them as the birds "hum" around the feeders.

We welcome you to come experience the peace and tranquility that our wonderful land has to offer.

name: Home in Los Gatos · ★4.97 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: What we love about our neighborhood is that we don't live in a neighborhood. Our house sits on a sunny hill top surrounded by the Redwood forest with the closest neighbor's house a couple hundred yards away. host_about:
Favorite quote: "Good looks, wealth and education are often wasted on the slow. Everything in moderation and moderation is the first to go."

Husband, father, avid downhill skier, motorcyclist, frustrated landscape artist and builder/craftsman, I enjoy creating things and the company of others. Empty twisty back roads, a firm suspension, and a good apex makes my motor rev. Uncrowded steeps covered in feet  of fluffy powder, blue sky, and mountain vistas are my favorite things. Hanging out with friends at our outdoor bar, drinking, eating, talking, laughing, enjoying the evening, reveling in the beauty that surrounds us. 

We offer a private guest suite (1 or 2 rooms), in a quite, beautiful setting. A romantic get-away, relaxing weekend, a place at the bar after a day of mountain biking, a family vacation adventure or whatever you choose, we'll do our best to accommodate your needs and style. Join us for a marguerita while watching a spectacular sunset on the deck, or enjoy a bottle of the superb local wines with your lover while watching the sun set in your window. Get to know us, share your experiences and find out what you might want to try while you're the area or have a private evening, just let us know what you desire.

name: Home in Davenport · ★4.70 · 1 bedroom · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Taco Tues. & Thurs with live music, Some very good acts.
host_about: Hey there folks, my name is Michael. I operate a small villa with a front private house, and a one bedroom bungalow. They are both fully self contained. We usually have an eclectic type of person that stays here, mostly artists, musicians, and alternative, progressive thinkers. These interesting  people are drawn to this electric area maybe because we have giant redwood trees behind us and the Pacific Ocean in front of us. I live here and it's my job to make sure everyone is happy. Some nights the whole place will be full of travelers eating together, playing music, and telling story. Other nights a quite family of four arrives just to get away from the New York winter. In Davenport with a population of three hundred you get to know everybody quick. The local pub and bakery have two community events every week its quite a hoot. I'm 40 and love the area , born and raised in these hills and know every great hiking trail, every great surf spot, every great and marvelous thing to do and see in this area. We have a fun basket of toys and game equipment thats been donated by travelers and has accumulated over time , so we have wet suits and surf boards to frisbees and golf clubs.  My days are full  tending to the traveler and everyday I'm grateful to have the opportunity to share with people the villa space and all the beautiful things this area has to offer. This has taken almost half a life time to attain. I have traveled the world and lived in other places but I always find myself back in the Santa Cruz area. I know it, love it, and have this great job of sharing it. If anyone out there wants the front line tour, I can accommodate or if you just choose  a cozy private night by the fire i can accommodate that. Like the beat of the ocean outside the villa, we march to our happy places that pull us away from our everyday grind, and I believe, this is the marching grounds for peace, happiness, well being, and adventure....  see ya soon   Michael

name: Home in Scotts Valley · ★4.91 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Scotts Valley is a small, quiet, walkable/bike-able town far enough away to leave behind the hub-bub of traffic and congestion of more populated areas - but with great freeway access to launch daytrips to the North or South.

We have 3 full size grocery markets, drug stores, coffee shops (Peets, Starbucks, cruz coffee), a renowned skatepark and a fabulous seasonal farmers market on Saturday mornings. Though there is not really much "night life" in our fair city - we do have several brewpubs and wineries which offer music and tastings / specialty food carts. Felton also has the Roaring Camp steam train, great hiking and a zip line park as well.

Our neighborhood is quiet and well-kept, with very little thru traffic and our home has several fruit trees and vegetable patches to enjoy seasonally.
host_about: I am a semi-retired Silicon Valley marketing professional who takes any opportunity to hit the great outdoors - which could include anything from picking wild berries in my neighborhood, to trekking the John Muir Trail. Though I am often away from the home, I pride myself on being highly responsive to any issues or questions that arise during my guests' stay.

name: Home in Ben Lomond · ★4.94 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
We are located in the mountains of Santa Cruz County with the city of Santa Cruz just a 20 minute drive away. There are numerous attractions and activities in the area including hiking in old growth redwoods or to the Lime Kilns, the Santa Cruz Boardwalk, ocean beaches and cliff walking, paddle boating in the reservoir, and Kayak rentals. University of California, Santa Cruz is nearby. Near the border of Scotts Valley and Santa Cruz lies the Mystery Spot, where the rules of gravity are seemingly altered. There are excellent restaurants in the small towns in the valley where we live, as well as in the larger county.

And, speaking of Santa Cruz County, locals know that the Santa Cruz Mountains Appellation is one of the oldest wine-growing regions in the United States. Family-owned wineries here produce stellar lots of Zinfindel, Cabernet Savignon, Pinot and Chardonnay, and the area has existed before Napa Valley became a wine region. Near here are Hallcrest, Zayante, Kissed b
host_about:

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.83 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:

You can leave your car in the driveway and walk to the beach, Boardwalk, Yacht Harbor or any the neighborhood shops including Betty's Burgers (grass fed), Linda Seabreeze Cafe (great breakfast), Seabright Brewery (pints of local brew), Brady's Yacht Club (great dive bar), Java Junction (free WiFi), Verve Cafe (beans roasted onsite), La Posta Restaurant, Tramonti (Italian style pizza) and others.

Please note: The City of Santa Cruz charges an 11% occupancy tax of all stays. This tax is not included in our rates and will be charged to guest as a separate supplementary amount thru Airbnb.

When I’m not travelling for work I enjoy fitness activities with my beautiful other half Denise. Any weekend we get to sneak away is spent in Santa Cruz relaxing and enjoying the beach, and on the occasion we get a free week we love to expand our view of the world and explore the amazing people and cultures on different continents.

I am married to Dale, and we have raised 3 children.  
-- I get a kick out of people having a good time at our place, interested in such a variety of things, coming together serendipitously at Redwood Croft.  Of course, quiet retreats are invited, too. This could be my motto:  "Stay open; Stay responsible."

host_about:

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.82 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath

It's a quiet residential neighborhood but still with quick and easy access to beaches, boardwalk and downtown.
host_about: We love the outdoors, hiking, cycling and camping.   We are musicians and enjoy living in Santa Cruz with all the arts and music that it offers.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.89 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2.5 baths

"You may call me a dreamer, but I'm not the only one."

For the beach visits, we are 1 mile from the boardwalk and west cliff beaches and there are multiple bike paths to get you to the beach from our location. It is a 20 minute walk to the Boardwalk and 20-25 minute walk to Lighthouse Beach.

Our street is near the local high school and
host_about: We are a four person eco-hippie, music loving family - Erin, Justin Satyana and  Indie. We love where we live - beaches, Redwoods, great people, amazing food, sunshine and the west coast vibe.

There are excellent restaurants in the small towns in the valley where we live, as well as in the larger county.

And, speaking of Santa Cruz County, locals know that the Santa Cruz Mountains Appellation is one of the oldest wine-growing regions in the United States. Family-owned wineries here produce stellar lots of Zinfindel, Cabernet Savignon, Pinot and Chardonnay, and the area has existed before Napa Valley became a wine region. Nancy's  has retired at the University of California (Santa Cruz). She wants to spend more time with the grandkids, doing water aerobics, visiting with friends and gardening.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.77 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths

name: Rental unit in Aptos · ★4.83 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath

The hot tub is available for an additional fee. It is located on the Penthouse Loft on the third floor of this home. It is next to the sunroom, with a BBQ, firepit, tables, chairs, lounging areas, and changing room. All to yourselves!

name: Loft in Santa Cruz · ★4.80 · 3 bedrooms · 6 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: We LOVE downtown Santa Cruz! The farmers market is directly across the street every Wednesday afternoon along with a fantastic flea market the second Sunday of every month. The  Beach Boardwalk is 1 mile away with world class surfing all along the coast.
host_about: Coastal Californian. Lover of travel, design, art, music, film, garden, food and many other forms of creativity. Hard work pays off.

name: Guesthouse in Santa Cruz · ★4.88 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:

It is 3 miles down the mountain to a nice beach. The roads around us don't have a lot of cars so the area is great for bicycling. Go north on Highway One and you are at Davenport, an old whaling town with a nice restaurant and another nice beach. Just further north on the coast is Ano Nuevo State Park, where the giant elephant seals raise their babies on the beach each spring. Also close by are Big Basin State Park (unfortunately temporarily shut after the fires), Wilder Ranch State Park, Henry Cowell State Park and many other great parks.

And of course, we are only 13 miles north of the wonderful town of Santa Cruz.

Note that we have 3 other units on the property, but they are all separated by plenty of space.
host_about:
My day job is investing in technology, hosting startup events and I do some consulting.  But my wife and I also have this magical place in the Santa Cruz mountains, in a clearing amongst the redwoods, next to a great winery, and only 3 miles from the beach.   We have our own pond, and we have surrounded ourselves with fruit trees and floral gardens, which we hope you will enjoy.  When we are not around, our caretaker, Ed Olson, takes care of our guests.  

We hope to create a Shangri-la feel for our guests - totally relaxed in the mountains and nature, but with all the comforts of home.  We are also frequent travelers, so we know how important it is to feel at home when staying in new accomodations.

name: Home in Bonny Doon · ★4.83 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2 baths

STARBUCKS one block away, there is a great Sunday Farmer's Market across the street, several good restaurants in walking distance.  Mini mart /  Mexican taqueria “Los Periscos Market" just two streets away.
host_about:
Beach home owned by three families that love the Santa Cruz community,  water sports, and all the wonders the ocean has to offer!

FUN History:  The house was nicknamed  "Ansel's Getaway" as ANSEL ADAMS was friends with the original owner of the home, John Bei.  Ansel and John would hang out in the basement smoking cigars and discussing leather tanning projects.  At the time, Ansel and John worked together at a local leather tannery shop creating camera cases of course!  According to the Bei grandchildren, Ansel was quite a character and a frequent visitor of the home.  

We have had a few artists visit Ansel's Getaway that have been artistically inspired during their stay.  Their work is displayed at the beach house.

name: Guesthouse in Santa Cruz · ★4.90 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
My neighborhood is quiet and surprisingly, at the back of the yacht harbor which is six blocks away. There are great local restaurants, bakeries and shops as well as the Rio Theater nearby. There is even a Roller Rink, which also has Jazzercise. Pacific Cultural Center is two blocks away, with Yoga and Feldenkrais classes available. The “Bicycle Trip “bike shop rents bicycles and is near by. It is easy to get to downtown, and everything is close by bike. We are not far from eight art movie screens and there are an additional 13 movie screens in town. The Rio Theater and Crepe Place have live music and are a short walk away! The Kuumbwa Jazz club downtown presents world class acts.

DO not leave valuables in your car...there is a lot of pedestrian traffic and you don’t want to invite theft!
host_about:
I love to garden, travel and enjoy good food. I love music ( our local Jazz club, the Kuumbwa is amazing!)  I am also a dancer, and love to move in many ways. Paris, Prague, London, Florence and Sienna are favorite places abroad, NYC , Portland, Nashville are good in the States.

As a hostess, I am pretty hands off... will love to show you on a map, our local farmer's markets, where the good local restaurants are and how to walk to the harbor ( four blocks from the house) and beach. I like things clean and simple; prefer the outdoors or a big city. There is no TV in the house, but a great sound system...I speak French fluently, can get by, barely, in German, Italian and Spanish.

Success is failure turned inside out–
The silver tint of the clouds of doubt,

host_about:

Life is too short, we must embrace one another, eat well, live well, and play hard!!!
You can find me in my garden, hiking with my pups… or cruising the coast on my Elliptigo (stand up bike)..

name: Bungalow in Aptos · ★4.82 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath

Enjoy dining at local restaurants, cafes and deli. Nearby you’ll find a fishing pier, Seacliff State Park Museum, golf course, Forest of Nisene Marks State Park, wineries, restaurants, antique shops and a small movie theater. Other nearby beach communities include Santa Cruz (10-12 minutes), Capitola (5-7 minutes), as well as Monterey and Carmel to the south (45-50 minutes). Aptos is central to each of these locations and surrounded by many wonderful state parks, beaches and attractions, including the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk.
host_about:
currently landlocked californian, but heart always at the coast. love traveling to kauai (our favorite family destination) - the hawaiian islands are so incredibly beautiful and we feel at home. other favorite destinations include australia, italy, lake tahoe and big sur.  favorite restaurant is momofuku in NY, but favorite food hands down is the ahi poke counter at foodland in princeville (amazing selection and great price). 

as a host, want to ensure guests are comfortable and make the most of their stay. my husband and I grew up in the bay area and frequented santa cruz - so we love to share our favorite beaches, activities, restaurants and shops. we are super friendly with our local neighbors so it's important that our guests are respectful and treat our home with care.

name: Place to stay in Aptos · ★4.95 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath

Our home is located next to Nisene Marks State Park. Our home is in the woods facing south with plenty of sun exposure. You will feel as if you are miles away from the rush of life, although you will only be two miles from the Village of Aptos. You will find a few interesting shops, cafes, wine tasting and a variety of restaurants. You can also walk out your door and be surrounded by coastal redwoods!

The addition of the Hot Springs hot tub requires more cleaning time. The filters are cleaned, pH is balanced and the water is kept at the correct level of chlorination before each new guest arrives. The water will be clear and clean for you, hopefully it will be that way when you leave.

The drive to our home is along a narrow road that follows Aptos Creek, so as a creek will curve so does the road to our home. There are towering redwoods, wildlife frequently cross the road, so please drive slowly and enjoy the beautiful two mile drive!

There are no stre

Come, relax, share your story and add on to your memories!

name: Guest suite in Santa Cruz · ★4.82 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is a relatively quiet neighborhood with an assortment of people who enjoy living near the beach--including long-time residents, families, retired people, UCSC students, and surfers interspersed to keep it characteristic of Santa Cruz.
Two blocks away is a modest shopping center which hosts the local farmer's market on Sunday mornings. A handful of eateries and a coffee shop, from fast food to upscale dining, line the two blocks toward the beaches. A back way to the beach (our special secret) is three lovely blocks, two of which are walking/biking trails, one lined with Cypress trees, and the next along a lagoon lined with Eucalyptus trees. Wonderful Farmer's Market across 17th Street on Sunday mornings is not to be missed!
The Harbor and Crows Nest restaurant and nightclub are a several blocks to the west along the shore. Downtown Santa Cruz is 3 miles west and Capitola, a quaint seaside town, is 2 miles east. Both are easily accessible by bike lanes, public
host_about: We, Peter & Marie, are a married couple who relish offering our sweet space & location to guests. We enjoy living in a tranquil atmosphere and want to share this with others of like mind at our home, Jasmine Garden Oasis Retreat House near the Sea. It is a modest home tucked away in a modest neighborhood three blocks from the beach in east Santa Cruz with two independent Airbnb studios upstairs, and expand to include the whole house when we offer guided retreats. We keep gentle gardens and cosy comfortable atmosphere for people who want a time of  renewal for body and soul. Often we enjoy the short tree-lined walk to visit the quiet beach and listen to the surf,  especially at dawn and dusk. name: Home in Aptos · ★5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Aptos is a small and very unique coastal town. We are close to downtown Santa Cruz and an easy drive to San Francisco, Monterey, Carmel and Big Sur.
host_about: I enjoy family , gardening and the beach .

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.77 · 3 bedrooms · 5 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
You will be able to walk from the front door to West Cliff Drive in under 3 minutes. The wharf is just another 5 minutes, and then you have the Boardwalk and Cowell's beach another couple of minutes from there. There are several wonderful restaurants on the wharf. During the summer months you will find salsa dancing and live outdoor music at the Ideal bar and grill located at the entrance of the wharf. There are also free Friday night concerts at the boardwalk. from June til September.
If you bring your dog there is a great walk the other direction on west cliff towards the lighthouse and surfing museum at lighthouse field. Mitchell's Cove has off leash hours for free running, and Frisbee. About a 10 minute walk to the lighthouse. West cliff drive takes you from the wharf all the way to natural bridges beach.

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.69 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: I love walking down the creek to the beach and the walkway to Sea Cliff Beach Pier and looking out at the Shipwreck. Love sitting outside at Cafe Rio and ordering the grilled artichoke. This area is pretty mellow and the ocean really is a marine sanctuary. I always see seals by the shore and dolphins frolicking about and certain times of the year loads of whales. Free admission to Sea World out there and with the birds and everything it's like something out of National Geographic at times.
host_about:
No act of kindness,
no matter how small,
is ever wasted.
   - AESOP

Favorite travel destinations include:
Azores Islands, Portugal - I could be a bit bias here, as my family is from the beautiful island of Pico, Azores. 
I was very fortunate to have backpacked on my own for 9 months all throughout SE Asia, New Zealand, Australia, Nepal and Hong Kong and love every one of these places. It was the best time of my life.

Single mom, woman owned small business owner. 

Thank you for your support!

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.84 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2 baths

name: Guest suite in Aptos · ★4.96 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The Rio del Mar / Aptos area allows you to be close to nature while still having all the conveniences of a charming town. It's also a great base for exploring the Central Coast - Monterey and Carmel are just a half-hour away!

From our place you can walk for miles along the beach, and you will often see dolphins, seals, all kinds of sea birds, and even whales right from the shore. You can also walk to restaurants, bars and cafes in Rio del Mar and Seacliff Village, or drive about a mile to find shopping, restaurants, and grocery stores in Aptos Village. Capitola-by-the-Sea, Downtown Santa Cruz, and the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk all just about 10-15 minutes away by car.

Just a little over a mile away there is awe-inspiring hiking among the redwoods at Nisene Marks park. Kayak rentals and whale watching trips are available nearby out of the Santa Cruz Harbor and also at Moss Landing. Drive about 15 minutes from here for wonderful wine tasting in Soquel or Corralito
host_about:
A Bay Area native, my heart has always belonged to the beach! I studied at UC Santa Cruz and in 2014 relocated to Aptos from San Francisco. I love exploring the area on foot with my husband Andy and our dog, Betty - ask me about our favorite walking routes! I'm a fan of the arts and you can often find me watching live music or a dance performance, locally or in San Francisco. 

I look forward to meeting you!

name: Guest suite in Santa Cruz · ★4.78 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: An incredible location and neighborhood, truly our favorite in Santa Cruz. Block and a half to beaches and surf. 4 blocks from pleasure point and right in the middle between Capitola village and the boardwalk.

name: Guest suite in Aptos · ★4.85 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.67 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: We love that the neighborhood is quiet and safe, the air is clean, and that there are hiking trails walking distance from the house and the beach is only 2 miles away.

name: Rental unit in Santa Cruz · ★4.80 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.98 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath

Magnolia Garden Bungalow is also a 5 min walk down to Capitola,  a charming Oceanside European style, village, where you can choose from a variety of delicious food, including Pizza ( Pizza My Heart; voted # 1 in the world) to go for a meal on the beach. The neighborhood stays cool on warm days with a bay breeze, not the big winds off the open ocean. Enjoy the front yard with a lush garden or the side yard with a barbecue. Both yards have Teak tables and chairs to relax for meals and drinks.
host_about: I've lived in Santa Cruz for about 45 years and enjoy the beauty and variety of beaches, restaurants, and the  ambiance of a resort town. The opportunity to ride my bike or walk to nearby restaurants is a plus for me and I know guests love the location. I am an Animal Portrait Painter, gardener, and ride my horse (Dressage). So I enjoy hosting and meeting people and their dogs/animals that come to visit.

name: Guesthouse in Santa Cruz · ★4.97 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.94 · 3 bedrooms · 6 beds · 2 baths

name: Guesthouse in Santa Cruz · ★4.75 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath

Drive or bike a short two miles and you are at the Santa Cruz Boardwalk and Wharf or check out the new Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary Exploration Center.   Walk along West Cliff and watch the surfers take on waves at the famous Steamers Lane or vist the surf museum at the Lighthouse. I could go on and on.  Santa Cruz is a fun place to visit and we are in a fun location to achieve that.
host_about:
I live in Santa Cruz, CA with my husband and spend a good deal of time at this beautiful place in Yelapa Mexico. I love being able to share Casa Luna with people. It's a magical house and it's an honor to share it. 
We love traveling to unique places in the world and love the fact that airbnb is almost everywhere.

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.85 · 4 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2.5 baths

host_about: We are a family that  loves people, travel, and exploration. I love to hike and be outdoors - do I live in the right place or what?

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.82 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath

name: Condo in Aptos · ★4.66 · 2 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2.5 baths

name: Condo in Aptos · ★4.85 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.94 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Walk to West Cliff Drive.
Walk to beaches.
Lovely neighbors.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.89 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths

host_about: I'm an art teacher, world traveler, book lover, foodie, dancer, gardener and mother. I love raising my family in Santa Cruz. I feel blessed to live where the forest meets the sea. I am excited to share my home with you!

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.88 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
Live Oak is an unincorporated mid county area situated between the cities of Santa Cruz and Capitola extending from Pleasure Point at the coast to the village of Soquel! Our home is a 5 minute bike ride from the beach and close to the surfing mecca of famed Pleasure Point breaks and the Yacht Harbor. Close by is the upper yacht harbor entrance to the new bike/bridge path across Arana Gulch that is both scenic and fun.
Santa Cruz is a unique and special place that can revive your spirit quickly, especially here on this beautiful Santa Cruz property!
host_about:
Former California Highway Patrolman and VP of Sales and Marketing for Pacific Cookie Co. Grandfather to ten including now 12 year-old twin grandsons who live in the South Bay of LA. Love the ocean, both in it and on it, gardening, biking, walking in beautiful Santa Cruz, especially along the new E. Cliff Ave walkway or Arana Gulch!
After leaving the highway patrol, I took a path that essentially went from CHiPS to chocolate chips!
Author and Founder of DriversYoga and Nowhere Yoga both 
 are mental technique to keep you in the moment while driving. My guidebook, The Art of Looking Through the Windshield can be purchased from Amazon.
Most say I get along well with being a very genial host.
You can talk to me about Nowhere Yoga!
Over the years we have created a mature and unique garden landscape full of beauty and sound in the mode of a zen temple sanctuary between the cities of Santa Cruz and Capitola. A visual stress remover! Come and experience, we're here for you. A relaxed self download if you will! 
Following the earthquake of 1989 we purchased 8K handmade bricks from the demo site of the downtown Oddfellow's building. (next door to the Cooper House building, now O'Neill's Surf. The bricks were vertical from the date of 1893 to 1989! So while here you are walking on a lot of Santa Cruz history and the building that housed the original town clock!
Airbnb ask me to tell guest if I have a life motto. Well yes in fact I do;  
Flexible indecision with all seriousness aside and forward to the rear"!  "It's always 'the ole same space"
And if you come, welcome to Santa Cruz---The gem of the central coast—-A special place! 
Aloha and Namaste
STORM UPDATE : At 5:12 AM on January 9 during 80 mph gale force winds our 90 ft. heritage Douglas Fir tree was pushed down!
Hopefully by June the ground can support the crane needed to lift this immense weight-tree has 48 inch diameter! Guest can walk thru a cut pass way to the labyrinth. Tree was the tallest on Chanticleer Ave. Also a large sinkhole evolved and repairs are underway!

name: Cottage in Santa Cruz · ★4.77 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath

name: Rental unit in Aptos · ★4.81 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
We love the neighborhood of Rio Del Mar in Aptos.
Nice walk to the the beach; depending on the time of the year, you can see dolphins migrating back and forth from Monterey Bay to Santa Cruz in the morning and late afternoon.
If hiking & biking 🚴‍♀️ are your cup of tea , Nisene Marks Forest is a great spot, and only 4 minutes from the house.

The restaurants are nearby : Cafe Sparrow in the APTOS Village and Cafe Rio down by the beach , to name just a couple. Many more fun restaurants available!

Carmel and Monterey is only 40 minutes south of Aptos. Santa Cruz 15 minutes north of us. San Francisco 45 minutes north of us.
host_about:
I love to live by the waters, whether it be by the ocean or by the lake.  
I love to cook and hosts friends. Friends & families are what makes life richer, meaningful and fun! 
I love to travel and see new places & learn different cultures, food & wine & of course, the people.

Blessings to you.

name: Guest suite in Santa Cruz · ★4.82 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is a relatively quiet neighborhood with an assortment of people who enjoy living near the beach--including long-time residents, families, retired people, UCSC students, and surfers interspersed to keep it characteristic of Santa Cruz.
Two blocks away is a modest shopping center which hosts the local farmer's market on Sunday mornings. A handful of eateries and a coffee shop, from fast food to upscale dining, line the two blocks toward the beaches. A back way to the beach (our special secret) is three lovely blocks, two of which are walking/biking trails, one lined with Cypress trees, and the next along a lagoon lined with Eucalyptus trees.
The Harbor and Crows Nest restaurant and nightclub are a several blocks to the west along the shore. Downtown Santa Cruz is 3 miles west and Capitola, a quaint seaside town, is 2 miles east. Both are easily accessible by bike lanes, public transportation and car.
host_about: We, Peter & Marie, are a married couple who relish offering our sweet space & location to guests. We enjoy living in a tranquil atmosphere and want to share this with others of like mind at our home, Jasmine Garden Oasis Retreat House near the Sea. It is a modest home tucked away in a modest neighborhood three blocks from the beach in east Santa Cruz with two independent Airbnb studios upstairs, and expand to include the whole house when we offer guided retreats. We keep gentle gardens and cosy comfortable atmosphere for people who want a time of  renewal for body and soul. Often we enjoy the short tree-lined walk to visit the quiet beach and listen to the surf,  especially at dawn and dusk. We welcome our Airbnb guests to join us early mornings with either QiGong or meditation in the garden or at the nearby lagoon. We have a list of healing artists who have offered to deliver their services to our guests in their private rooms or in the garden.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.88 · 3 bedrooms · 5 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Very quiet neighborhood on a dead-end street, no thru traffic. Houses on our side of this street back up to Moran Lagoon. Beautiful views of green-belt and quick walk to the beach. Enjoy the views of the monarch butterflies and ducks while listening to the waves.

The house is a 5-10 minute walk to several area beaches for a fun day of surfing, boogie boarding, sunbathing, and relaxing. Surfers only have a short walk to enjoy the world class surf at Pleasure Point break, the Hook, 38th, Sharks, and 26.

The restaurants and shopping on Portola and 41st are just a 15-20 minute walk or 10 minute bike ride away (0.9 miles).

Capitola and The Harbor/Crow’s nest are both a 2 mile walk, (Please note they are in opposite directions.) Walking 30-40 minutes, biking 20 minutes, and a 5-7 minutes drive.

The Pleasure Point Market is a short walk away or there are a number of grocery stores within a 5-10 minute drive (Whole Foods, Trader Joe's, Safeway.)
host_about: We are a couple who owns several rental properties in the Bay Area and Santa Cruz.  We love to travel and welcome fellow travelers to our vacation rental home in Santa Cruz.  Some of our favorite things to do when in Santa Cruz is walking the beaches to Capitola during low tide and collecting, shells, driftwood, and beach glass or riding our bicycles all over town. We love traveling throughout Europe and especially Italy.  Our bucket list of near-future travel destinations are Spain, Portugal, Morocco and Ecuador & Colombia.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.76 · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Just 1.5 blocks from Pleasure Point! The most amazing spot to watch the surfers, walk the paved path along the beautiful cliffs or do some surfing! The other direction is 26 Avenue beach where you can sit in the sun, watch the surf, take a dip in the ocean, body surf, run the dogs on the beach, or have an evening fire! Bathrooms are located across the street in the parking area.

Just a short 10 minute drive or a long walk to Downtown Capitola! Food, beaches, shopping! Or just a great place for a stroll.

Just 15 minute drive to Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk. Fun under the sun! Games, rides, Miniature Golf, Arcade, or bowling. Walk the pier and see the fishermen bringing in their fresh haul! Great restaurants for all types of taste.

Want to go to a Farmer's Market? There is a fabulous one at Cabrillo College in Aptos just about a 20 minute drive from the house.

How about going to Downtown Santa Cruz and enjoy the color of the area?
host_about:
Our parents purchased Seahaven in 2000 as a home for our families and dear friends to come to enjoy the sights and sounds of Santa Cruz, the beauty of the Monterey Bay,  and and most of all to come together as a family to create lasting memories.  Which it did for us and then some!

We are so pleased to share the love and joy of Seahaven with others.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.90 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Great location. So close to the beach that you can see the ocean from the street. Very easy, quick beach access down 14th ave. Blacks Beach, Twin Lakes Beach and Sunny Cove all within short walking distance.

Walking distance to groceries, dining, Sunday farmers markets, harbor and more.
host_about:
We love surfing, biking, our beautiful beaches & redwoods.  We've been on Airbnb for 10 years and LOVE IT! We've made some great connections over the years & we have guests that return several times a year for fun and for business. Our goal is that you have a fantastic stay and we want to facilitate a great experiences and fun memories. 

We are inclusive and welcome guests of all orientations and backgrounds. Family Friendly. LGBTQ friendly.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.82 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Very friendly, quiet and upscale upper Westside neighborhood. Great to just walk or run around the neighborhood or to Pogonip (less than a 1 mile), a wonderful huge open space just below the university. It's very peaceful and everybody is friendly.

I also like going for a run at Pogonip (a big open space next to UCSC), right around the corner, or on West Cliff Drive at the beach, I enjoy SUPing alone and with friends. Gardening is my therapy and yoga is one of my passions, and Santa Cruz is perfect for it!  My favorite country is Thailand (I lived there for 6  months and even speak a little Thai) and my favorite city is Barcelona. I love living in beautiful Santa Cruz and I often say: I live in paradise!

name: Guest suite in Scotts Valley · ★4.86 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Our home is in a  quiet family neighborhood in a nice area of Scotts Valley. We have a great commute location to Silicon Valley (30 to 50 minutes or so) and superb hiking is nearby in Felton and Santa Cruz.  Santa Cruz is a 15 to 20 minute drive.  The Monterey Bay Aquarium and Carmel are a 1 hour drive.
host_about: I am a semi-retired Silicon Valley marketing professional who takes any opportunity to hit the great outdoors - which could include anything from picking wild berries in my neighborhood, to trekking the John Muir Trail. Though I am often away from the home, I pride myself on being highly responsive to any issues or questions that arise during my guests' stay.

name: Guest suite in Santa Cruz · ★4.96 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a unique mixture of residential, commercial, a school and a cool founder's cemetery nearby (quiet neighborhood). We don't have neighbors on either side (a tire shop on one side and a school on the other). We are within walking distance of the harbor and beach (20 minute walk). We are also close bicycle ride to most of Santa Cruz and Capitola.
host_about:
I live in Santa Cruz, California with my wonderful wife Katharina and our son Oliver. I am a professional Airbnb host and a former elementary school teacher and Katharina is an amazing person and an incredibly talented creative director. Oliver is a bright, energetic and friendly young man that loves the water, bike riding, history, exploring and solving the mysteries of the universe. We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★5.0 · 3 bedrooms · 5 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
From the website http://www.santacruz.org:

With colorful surf shops, charming beach cottages, and a shoreline teeming with surfers and beachgoers, Pleasure Point is the kind of quintessential beach community that enlivens Hollywood movies and lures envious tourists to California’s sunny shores. Situated on Santa Cruz’s east end, this seaside neighborhood is one of the most vibrant surf destinations along the California coast. The easy going ‘hood earned its hedonistic name from Prohibition-era shenanigans, but you’d swear it’s because spending a day here is such a joy, no surfboard required!

One of Pleasure Point’s biggest draws is East Cliff Drive, a dazzling waterfront promenade—part of the Monterey Bay Sanctuary Scenic Trail—that winds along coastal bluffs overlooking the sparkling Monterey Bay. Join the parade of beach cruisers, skaters, and board-toting surfers as you enjoy vistas of quiet beach coves and thrilling surf breaks.

You’ll spot a crowd

neighborhood_overview:

There are picnic tables in front of the Market where bicyclists and hikers may drop in for lunch or snacks.

A block further are both a tacquiria and pizza parlor. Drop in to eat at their picnic tables or take your food with you as you wander the country roads.

The roads are fairly quiet, flat with the odd hill. You will ride through old and new orchards, go by the berry farms that Driscoll has planted along Corralitos Road.

You may want to stop at Alladin Nursery on the corner of Corralitos and Freedom. They have a unique gift shop, fabulous flowers and plants owned by the same family for several genertions.

Roses of Yesterday down Brown's Valley Rd is an old, 1920's, family owned, peaceful, multiacre heritage rose garden. They host a special

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.83 · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 3 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The vacation rental (110 Quintana Ct). is located on the lower West side of Santa Cruz. It's a easy close walk to the beach and a 2.5 mile ocean bike/walking path. Located in the most desired part of town. The backyard faces south which means it gets full sun. People love the hot tub and firepit.
Close by to the house is the Swift Street court yard. It's a classy collection of six wine tasting rooms, Santa Cruz Mountain brewery, Kelly's bakery and one of our favorite restaurant's The West End Tap & Kitchen. There are many great supermarkets, restaurants and coffee shops close by.
The neighborhood is not congested like the east side of Santa Cruz and Live Oak. You can park your car at any hour and not have to worry about finding a spot. No permit or metered parking.
Located in a quiet small court. It's more private, less expensive and safer for kids than ocean front homes. You don't have cars and people constantly going by.
host_about: I moved to santa cruz in 95 because of the great outdoor activities. I love living by the ocean and the redwoods. I lived in the vacation house for 15 years and had some of the best times of my life. It's close to the best of Santa Cruz. Once I had my own family I wanted more of the country life. I moved to Bonnydoon located in the santa cruz mountains 15 minutes away.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.87 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths

I am happy to say the neighbors are all really friendly and we often stop to visit with each other. There is a coffee shop just around the corner called The Abbey, which is a great meeting place. Also close to Hwy 1 (Mission St) and Hwy 17 and 1.5 miles from Cowell Beach where you can surf, rent kayaks, or just walk along beautiful West Cliff Drive ..and 3.6 miles from Upper Wilder Ranch and amazing mountain bike trails.
The down hill traffic from UCSC can back up in front of the house as they wait to get onto Hwy 1. This usually occurs in the afternoon and doesn't last that long. The traffic in Santa Cruz in general has gotten a lot heavier in the afternoons everywhere. Since my house is very central, I do a lot of walking and biking. The walk to downtown is literally six blocks and highly recommended. There is an ever growing house manual with further descriptions and
host_about: I've lived in Santa Cruz for 26 years. It's been an amazing time and I'm still happy to be here. I was in Big Sur for several years before that so the Coast is Home. I'm happy and proud to host people in a beautiful and clean home which gives you access to life here that doesn't exist in a hotel room or constantly eating out. Your enjoyment is my mission.

name: Guest suite in Aptos · ★4.91 · Studio · 2 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The guests that we have had in the Hummingbird Haven & the Mushroom Dome Cabin are amazed by the quiet and peaceful nature of our area. At night, you will hear lots of crickets, maybe an owl or a tree frog and sometimes the ocean waves crashing in the distance. In the summer, you can see the Milky Way as we are far enough away from city lights that, on a clear night, you can see quite a lot of stars.
The Monterey Bay is one of the most vibrate marine sanctuaries in the world - sometimes hosting the largest gathering of marine mammals in the world. We have various whales here year round with whale watching tours daily. Check out our reviews of the Mushroom Dome Cabin to get feedback from our guests of our property. If you plan ahead, you can have a larger group here by reserving both spaces.
We also have a metal geodesic dome climbing structure, a small netted trampoline and a tiny playhouse for kids to play with.
host_about:
We live on 10 beautiful acres of sun, oak forest, redwood groves and gardens with a parrot, 2 cats, a small dog, 12 chickens and from 200 - 500 hummingbirds - depending on the time of year..  

I have been hosting on airbnb since July, 2009 and really love what this company has made possible. I have met so many wonderful people from around the world that I would never have met if I hadn't had this opportunity with airbnb! Some of our guests (especially the ones from Europe) have never seen a hummingbird before and here they get to see them up close - just a few feet from them as the birds "hum" around the feeders.

We welcome you to come experience the peace and tranquility that our wonderful land has to offer.

It's quiet and safe and there are many old Victorian style houses to view up and down the street. Walking distance to The Buttery, Whole Foods, Shoppers Corner, and Rite Aid, just to name a few.

name: Cottage in Santa Cruz · ★4.92 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The Seabright neighborhood is perfectly located between the boardwalk and the marina. Both are just under a mile from the cottage. It is warmer and sunnier than the rest of town and therefore called the "banana-belt" of Santa Cruz.

Seabright beach is your "classic beach". The wide sands stretch beneath the bluffs. The facilities are decent with flush toilets and an outdoor shower. Lifeguards keep you safe during the summer season. There are fire rings for evening bonfires.

There are a handful of restaurants in the heart of Seabright, and you are only a mile from all the shops and eateries on Pacific Street, downtown. You are in the middle of everything, yet living on a quiet neighborhood street, perfect for peaceful evenings at home.
host_about:
I love to travel. I've been to 4 continents, 20 countries, 39 states.
I like to count things :-) I take a lot of pictures. I am both a guest and host at AirBnB. I am quiet and respectful.

Once in town just park your car and walk everywhere you need to go. The beaches, food, store, church and post office are all within a three minute walk from the house. Feel like a great cup of coffee and fresh pastry during your morning walk on the beach? Davenport has the best bakery around! Craving a four star dinner to celebrate? Davenport can deliver! Wish to enjoy live music several nights of the week within a two minute walk? Again, this is available within walking distance. Is a wine tasting adventure on your list today? This is also available with just a short walk to the end of the block!

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.89 · 6 bedrooms · 6 beds · 3 baths
neighborhood_overview: My spacious downtown art filled vacation house is great for any occasion! Spend a few days at the beach with your family, go hiking in the beautiful local redwood forests,  or ride the Giant Dipper and enjoy a funnel cake at the Boardwalk. If the season is right, you can see the Monarch butterflies nest at Natural Bridges State Park.  You can get a seafood dinner with an ocean view on the wharf, take a stroll down the beautiful backdrop of West Cliff Drive, or if you would just like to enjoy some peace and quiet in a serene environment-- you've come to the right place! Its now an awesome, make-shift dog stop and if you have a doggie, I'm sure they will find it full of smells of the neighborhood dogs. The beach is literally 3 blocks down the road and the sunset walks are a must for everyone on the block - we all grab a glass of wine and head down to the cliffs with doggies in tow. host_about: I am a practicing fine artist. I work in both paint and print, with an etching press in my studio. Additionally I still occasionally do landscape architecture and design projects. I love to garden and cook as well. My husband and I have been living here in the Monterey Bay Area for more than 25 years. I grew up in the San Francisco Bay Area. We like to greet our guests when they arrive to familiarize them with details about the place. We have been avid tennis players but now spend more time with golf. We try to give our guests as much privacy as possible and that's pretty easy since the suite is not only private because of it's design, but because the area we live in is semi-rural and quiet. Trees abound. The one acre property backs up to a 20 acre forest and orchard. Our road is one of the most popular cycling routes in the county.

host_about:
Combined Myriam and Mikey have lived in Santa Cruz for over 35 years. We have 3 young children ages 3, 5, and 7, and spend a lot of our free time tromping in the forests here in Santa Cruz, running, going to the beach, gardening, and reveling in large cooking projects using our local bounty of available foods.

We purchased this property  to have as a getaway for us and our friends, and vacationers like yourself. This property is so close to Rio del Mar beach, so it's just a short 2 minute walk back home if you forget sunscreen, or you want to cook up lunch, etc. The house is comfortable, with modern, brand new amenities. An extensive total remodel was just recently completed, so all of the appliances, bathroom fixtures, etc are nearly brand new.

This house is a perfect home for a family or 1 or 2 couples to have a relaxing weekend so close to one of the best (if not the best!) beach on the central coast. You can walk this beach for miles in either direction, it is not very crowded, and the weather here is never too hot and never too cold. Rio del Mar feels like a small beach town, yet it is 10 miles to Santa Cruz, and less than 40 miles from the Silicon Valley.

The Forest of the Nisene Marks State Park, and lots of other parks, as well as all the other wonderful beaches that this area has to offer are also within a 5 to 25 min. drive.

The latest addition to the neighborhood: the Brazilian brewery and kitchen: Woodhouse: a mere 2 blocks away and boasts live music most weekends. :)

name: Guest suite in Soquel · ★4.90 · 2 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The immediate neighborhood has sparse housing (minimum parcel size is 5 acres). If you need to get away from the hustle and bustle of the cities, suburbs or even beach area congestion, this is the place to be. Once you are well-rested, there's a variety of interesting things to do and places to eat in the vicinity. We especially like:

* Capitola Beach (4.5 mi) - order a slice of pizza from Pizza My Heart, sit on a sidewalk bench and gaze out onto the ocean and beachfront. There are also numerous restaurants and bars that will keep you occupied. Try Margarita Ville for their great assortment of margaritas and appetizers. Stop off at nearby Gayle's Bakery for some delicious deli food and desserts.

* Pacific Avenue, Santa Cruz (6.5 mi) – what would a visit to Santa Cruz be without a stroll down Pacific Avenue in downtown Santa Cruz? The street is iconic for its progressive nature and rivals Berkeley for honors as the ultimate “left coast” university town. Not exact
host_about: We are Greg and Naima Hyver. We would love to share our home with you in the beautiful Santa Cruz mountains. Get away from the hustle and bustle of the downtown area, yet still be within 5 minutes of it.

name: Cottage in Santa Cruz · ★4.91 · 2 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The house is centrally located to all the attractions in Santa Cruz.
Three miles away is the main attraction in Santa Cruz, the California Beach Boardwalk. The boardwalk has rides, events and attractions right on the beach. One mile away is Twin Lakes Beach. There you will find the Yacht Harbor, which offers beach volleyball, kayaks rentals and wonderful restaurants also on the beach. Two miles in the opposite direction is Capitola. Capitola is a quaint beach town, with many restaurants and boutique shops. Pleasure Point, which is a popular surf area and 41st Ave, which is filled with restaurants and surf shops, is 1 mile away.
Santa Cruz is apart of the Monterey Bay, which has endless possibilities for sight seeing. One of the most popular is the Monterey Bay Aquarium in Monterey and Carmel, which is 45 miles away.
Silicon Valley is 30 min to 1 hour away depending on which town you want to go to. The other benefit to the house is the new Levi stadium is 35 minut
host_about: We are the Talbot family. We bought our vacation home when our kids were 9 and 12. We wanted a place we could enjoy the beach, but also share that experience with others like you.  We wanted to embrace the Santa Cruz lifestyle with a beach house-style home.    I was born and raised in Hawaii, and I wanted a home away from home. So the island decor fits perfectly with the house location to the surf, beach, and the Aloha Grill down the street.  Our kids love the bunk beds, and we made one of the rooms into a surfer decor to bring the Santa Cruz surf style to life. The beach, which is a short walk away, was perfect for beach lovers alike.  It has boogie boarding, surfing, great sand for sandcastles, and wonderful views. The beach has no public parking, so it is inhabited by mostly locals and doesn't get too crowded. Also, at night it is a great beach for bonfires.  We hope you enjoy the house!

name: Camper/RV in Felton · ★4.94 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
When staying in our trailer, you two will have easy access to the best Felton and nearby Santa Cruz have to offer!

Henry Cowell State Park: 5 min walk
Monty's Log Cabin, closest bar: 5 min walk
Wild Roots Market, health food store: 15 min walk (2 min drive)
The Grove, best restaurant in Felton: 15 min walk (2 min drive)
Hallcrest Vineyards, closest wine tasting room: 20 min walk (4 min drive)
Roaring Camp Railroads: 20 min walk (8 min drive)
Santa Cruz: 20 min drive via Highway 9
Davenport, closest beach with no crowds: 30 min drive via Felton Empire
host_about:
We are a young(ish) couple living in a 1937 summer cabin in the redwood forest and mountains above Santa Cruz. We have a daughter Lucy, born March 2019. She sometimes joins our travels.

Nate is engine house manager at a local railroad, Brianna is a transportation planner. We love tending vegetables and flowers, sailing, cooking lavish meals, long hikes with our puppy, getting lost, wine tasting (including in a brown bag), reading in the sunshine, and most of all traveling! We've visited dozens of countries all over the world, but are also excited to discover new places close to home.

name: Guest suite in Scotts Valley · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath

We are hoping you will make our guest unit your “home away from home” during your stay with us. Our mountain property in the redwoods will provide you with the perfect opportunity to unwind and relax during your travels!

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.72 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: Great Neighborhood! Home is located in a rural, hilly area at the top of a slope overlooking the ocean and the mountains. No through traffic, nice and slow, safe with friendly neighbors. The Town of Aptos has cafés, restaurants, natural foods market and a beach resort open to the public. Some of the most beautiful beaches on the Central Coast are here: deep, wide, quiet, and bordered by beautiful cliff-scapes.
host_about:
**Minority Guests Welcome**  I've been Super hosting for 11 years now and I really enjoy sharing my home in beautiful Aptos.
Guests share kitchen, living room and dining rm. w/host and sometimes another guest. Shared kitchen supplies include coffee, tea, cooking herbs & spices, cooking oil. I love to visit and am comfortable giving guests whatever space they need.  I'm a very quiet night owl; I'll be up late but you won't hear me.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.90 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Located in a quiet neighborhood at the south-end of Downtown Santa Cruz, close to schools, the beach, dining and shopping.

Leisurely walk to downtown, Boardwalk, Wharf, Cowell’s and Main Beach. Great groceries, farmer's market, cafes, and restaurants within walking distance. Fun bike ride to West Cliff or to the Santa Cruz Harbor.
host_about:
We are a family of four. We enjoy hosting Airbnb guests from around the world! 

Located downtown Santa Cruz. We are only a short 5-10 minute walk to the beach and Boardwalk! 

We offer “hosted” accommodations. This means that we live here and manage our vacation rental spaces! 

Sycamore Park Property Management Company - offering furnished long term, medium term and short term rentals.  

We enjoy travel for water and snow fun!

name: Guesthouse in Santa Cruz · ★4.93 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
We are in the mountains surrounded by redwoods, meadows and a winery. 1 mile up the road is an ecological preserve with great hiking. It is 3 miles down the mountain to a nice beach. The roads around us don't have a lot of cars so the area is great for bicycling. Go north on Highway One and you are at Davenport, an old whaling town with a nice restaurant and another nice beach. Just further north on the coast is Ano Nuevo State Park, where the giant elephant seals raise their babies on the beach each spring. Also close by are Big Basin State Park (unfortunately shut down temporarily after the fires), Wilder Ranch State Park, Henry Cowell State Park and many other great parks.

And of course, we are only 13 miles north of the wonderful town of Santa Cruz.

Note that we have 3 other units on the property, but they are all separated by plenty of space.
host_about:
My day job is investing in technology, hosting startup events and I do some consulting.  But my wife and I also have this magical place in the Santa Cruz mountains, in a clearing amongst the redwoods, next to a great winery, and only 3 miles from the beach.   We have our own pond, and we have surrounded ourselves with fruit trees and floral gardens, which we hope you will enjoy.  When we are not around, our caretaker, Ed Olson, takes care of our guests.  

We hope to create a Shangri-la feel for our guests - totally relaxed in the mountains and nature, but with all the comforts of home.  We are also frequent travelers, so we know how important it is to feel at home when staying in new accomodations.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.94 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
Located on the far western edge of town, close to everything, but secluded from traffic and city congestion. This west side neighborhood is unique in Santa Cruz.

You will find great restaurants, enjoy picnics on the beach, discover local breweries and wine tasting within walking distance or a short easy drive. There is easy access to good food, weekly farmers market, yoga classes, meditation, hikes and ocean adventures.

Zen Garden Sanctuary is located just steps from West Cliff drive. A coastal promenade offering walkers, joggers, surfers room to move and observe the wildlife of the Monterey Bay.

Westside beaches, the Santa Cruz Wharf, the Light House, Steamers Lane, Natural Bridges State Park, and Seymour Marine Discovery Center are easily accessible by foot, bike or a short drive. Wilder Ranch is nearby with it's miles of spectacular hiking and bike trails and access to the north coast beaches. Downtown Santa Cruz is about 3 miles away, a short d
host_about: Arthur and I love sharing our environment with fellow adventurers. As frequent travelers, we  know what it is like to be on the road for long periods of time. Created  as a personal retreat, Zen Garden offers a peaceful place to return.  Coming home to the embrace of a welcoming, beautiful environment is always the best part of the journey. We offer our guests a safe, gentle place to land, to retreat and to explore–an environment you can enjoy as much as we do.  If Arthur is home, he  is  sure to share a moment with you or a tale of his recent travels around the world building community through rhythm. As a health care practitioner, I work to keep body, mind and spirit in balance. We are both writers and artists and enjoy sharing what we create with our visitors.

name: Home in La Selva Beach · ★4.94 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
Quiet, tranquil neighborhood with natural beauty. We are on a quiet cul-de-sac (road with no outlet) so there is almost no traffic. We're on over 1/3 acre that is beautifully landscaped and has oaks and pines. The town just 3-4 miles north of us is Aptos, which has cafes, several restaurants, grocery stores, and more, including Seascape Beach Resort (restaurants and shops) and Seacliff State Beach. Manresa State Beach is at the bottom of our hill (1.5 mile, 5-minute drive).

You will be in our guest suite with private entrance in our home while we are at home. There are no shared spaces.
host_about:
Hello! We live in Santa Cruz County near Manresa State Beach, and are excited about sharing our beautiful home and helping you enjoy all that the Monterey Bay area has to offer. 

We love to go out with our cameras to capture local life, including surfers in Santa Cruz and natural areas. We enjoy cooking, travel, and spending time with family and friends.

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.78 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
5-min drive. Visit Rio Del Mar State Beach, a beautiful stretch of sandy beach that's popular for swimming, surfing, and sunbathing.
5-min drive. Play a round of golf at the Seascape Golf Club, a challenging 18-hole course with panoramic ocean views.
5-min drive. Explore the Aptos Farmers Market, held every Saturday morning, to sample fresh local produce and other products from local farmers and vendors.
10-min drive. Take a hike at Manresa State Beach, which offers stunning views of the Pacific Ocean and a variety of trails for hikers of all levels.
18-min drive. Go birdwatching at Pajaro Dunes, a secluded beachfront community that's home to a wide variety of bird species.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.87 · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 3 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located on the Westside which is a quiet, friendly and safe neighborhood. Great for family gatherings but it is also an outdoor enthusiast's dream! It is the heart of the local surf culture and the wellspring of the distinctive Santa Cruz vibe.

It boasts some of the most beautiful beaches and coastal views in all of Santa Cruz. It is home to Steamer Lane, a world class surf spot. The Santa Cruz Surf Museum, Henry Cowell Redwood State Park, Wilder Ranch State Park, and 6 wine tasting rooms are also short distances away.

West Cliff Drive which is steps away from the house is the scenic route that travels along the coast. It has a two mile walking and biking path that stretches from the Santa Cruz Wharf to Natural Bridges State Park.

There is something for everyone in and around this house.
host_about:
I am an adventurous traveler and have a pretty cool tag-a-long named Riley, my daughter.  We’ve been fortunate to travel to off-the-beaten places to rock climb, backpack, hike and bike,  and snowboard.  Luckily, the Bay Area offers all of this within a reasonable driving distance!  

Airbnb is my first choice in lodging and we have never been disappointed.  I strive to provide the same experience for my guests and make your experience memorable.

host_about: I am a genuine product of japan, born, raised, educated and lived the first half of my life there. In 1982, I moved to California with and was adopted into the American culture. I appreciate expressions of all kinds – music, visual arts, dance, words.I like things that are aesthetically pleasing in shape, form, color and texture which I think is reflected in my cooking, my home and my garden. I love the creative process of taking different elements and creating something tasteful and elegant.

name: Guesthouse in Felton · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 0 shared baths
neighborhood_overview: We're not far from downtown Felton, a charming little mountain community with  several restaurants, 2 markets (one is a  natural foods store with fabulous organic local produce), a great music venue (Don Quixote's), and a sweet new age shop/bookstore (Mountain Spirit). There is an amazing farmer's market on Tuesdays May - September. You could hike for days and days at the local parks and recreation areas, or enjoy a stroll through this mountain neighborhood if you don't feel like driving to a trailhead.
host_about:
My partner Chris and I live in the Santa Cruz Mountains. Chris is a glass artist, and I manage a student program at UC Santa Cruz.  We love travel  whether to urban or outdoor locations but don't get to do enough of it! Still, in the past few years we made it to London, Oahu, Santa Fe, and the North Rim of the Grand Canyon.   In 2019 I visited India (Mumbai, Delhi, Agra) which was a real bucket-list destination for me. Other travel goals include France, Italy, South America, Bali, Greece, and Scandinavia.

We enjoy hosting and meeting new people through our listing, as well as when we travel. We are quiet and considerate guests and do our best to be welcoming hosts.

“When you come on something good, first thing to do is share it with whoever you can find. That way, the good spreads out to where no telling it will go.”

name: Guest suite in Soquel · ★4.87 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview: The home is in a small neighborhood in the hills of Soquel.   You will be about two miles from a a supermarket and CVS.  There is a gas station with a foodmart about 1/4 mile away.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.99 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located 2 blocks from the world class Pleasure Point surf spot. Pleasure Point offers expert to beginner surf. Moran Lagoon beach is a quick 5 minute walk from the house. Walking on the promenade of Pleasure Point is a must do! The path is a great spot to watch the surfers, walk the dog and enough the sunshine! Rock view, located also just 2 blocks away is a picture perfect place to watch the sunset. Pleasure Point is just like West Cliff Drive, only better!

The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk is a quick 10 minute drive from the house and is the downtown shopping area. Capitola Beach is a quick 5 minute drive, but it is also walkable and bikable.

From the house hiking, biking, adventuring is all right there. It is a great jumping off point for all that Santa Cruz County has to offer.
host_about: I never thought that I would be a professional Air BnB host, but when an unexpected injury retired me from my career as a firefighter, my side hustle as an Air BnB host became a bigger part of my life.  I channel my passion and commitment to excellence into my Air BnB hosting.  When I’m not hosting I love to travel.  Through the last 7 years of hosting I have had the pleasure to meet a ton of really cool people from all over the world!

name: Guesthouse in Santa Cruz · ★4.89 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Feel like a local in our neighborhood.  The bungalow is inside the Santa Cruz city limits.  Our neighborhood is  Seabright or  Midtown, one of the best and most desirable locations in Santa Cruz.  Listen to the waves and sea lions during the quiet evenings.  Approximately 10 minute walk/5 minute bike ride to the Santa Cruz Harbor, Arana Gulch open space is the closest hiking spot (just about a block away), Frederick Street Park, and excellent local restaurants, entertainment, natural history museum, grocery store, roller rink, post office, gas station, and all needed amenities, all within a casual walk. Seabright beach is close by too (15 minute or so bike ride).  Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk and downtown are also a 15 minute bike ride/30-40 min walk away. Fun, Sun, Sand, and Surf are awaiting you.
host_about: I am a fifth generation native Santa Cruzan. I divide my time between my painting studio and my art therapy practice, which usually keeps me pretty busy.  I look forward to sharing my space with you while you are here, and giving you lots of privacy to experience the very unique and inviting community of Santa Cruz and my sweet little bungalow.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.73 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2 baths
host_about:
We've been helping people make terrific Santa Cruz Memories for generations.  Let us assist in making your next beach vacation amazing.

Kendall & Potter was established as a real estate company over fifty years ago. 
The brokers Skipper Kendall and William Potter moved to Aptos to fulfill their dream of working in a small town in Santa Cruz County. They soon expanded their services to include property management and relocation to Santa Cruz County along the Monterey Coast.

Kendall & Potter continues to be seen as one of the leading forces in Santa Cruz County Real Estate Property Management.

Rita Law, now owner and broker, purchased the property department and has been on site for nearly 50 years.

Kendall & Potter Property Management offers a variety of home services – including complete property management services, leases on unfurnished properties and rental homes in Santa Cruz, as well as Monterey Coast & Santa Cruz vacation rentals management and corporate housing.

name: Guesthouse in La Selva Beach · ★4.90 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
We live in the country. Every time I step outside, I'm reminded of this in the animals I see right outside my back door. Deer, possums, hawks, owls, rabbits, mice, snakes, lizards, gophers, coyotes, you name it and you'll see it.... from the cute and awe inducing to the not so sweet and cuddly. There isn't a day that goes by that we don't see at lease one of the above mentioned critters.
Walk down to the beach and you'll be amazed at the shore birds, dolphins, otters, and whales that you can sometimes spot right from shore. We feel so lucky to live in such a magical place where we're constantly reminded of how amazing mother nature is.
host_about: We are a fun loving family who snowboards in the winter and surfs in the summer. We love to travel with our 3 kids, camping, exploring new restaurants, San Francisco, Tahoe, and our little slice of heaven in La Selva Beach.

host_about:
I live in Santa Cruz, California with my wonderful wife Katharina and our son Oliver. I am a professional Airbnb host and a former elementary school teacher and Katharina is an amazing person and an incredibly talented creative director. Oliver is a bright, energetic and friendly young man that loves the water, bike riding, history, exploring and solving the mysteries of the universe. We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.96 · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Seacliff State Beach:

Stairs at end of Beachgate Way (3 blocks away).  Walk 2 blocks back down Seacliff toward State Park Drive.  Right on Coates, follow it as it curves around to stairs at Beachgate.

3 mile running loop:  start from cement boat wharf and run North to cliffs at New Brighton Beach and return.

Use outdoor shower upon return, if necessary.

Capitola:

Take Hwy 1 North one exit to “Park Avenue”.  ~ 3/4 mile

Left at Exit (West”) onto Park Ave.  Follow Park Ave until it ends at Monterey / Bay Road.

Left onto Monterey down hill to downtown Capitola (good luck parking!)

Other Attractions:

name: Home in Aptos · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 3 baths
neighborhood_overview:
"The Seacliff Neighborhood of Aptos borders Seacliff State Beach. The heart is Seacliff Village, a small collection of shops and restaurants along Center Avenue. The most well known of these places are Manuel’s Mexican Restaurant (in business over 50 years) and Marianne’s Ice Cream.

The icon of the neighborhood has got to be the sunken concrete ship, the S.S. Palo Alto. The Palo Alto was towed to its present location and intentionally sunk in 1930. The idea was to create an amusement ship and tourist draw, but the enterprise went bankrupt two years after opening its doors. Seacliff remained a quiet, sleepy place until after World War II, when hundreds of summer homes began to spring up. The area residents have worked to keep the neighborhood largely quiet despite its growth, and today it remains a quaint seaside enclave, famous for its foggy summers." (aptoscommunitynews.org, Sebastian Frey)

name: Guesthouse in Santa Cruz · ★4.98 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our Farmhouse was built in 1932 during a thriving area for Live Oak as the crown jewel of hens and egg production. The chickens are gone but their history has left us with rich fertile soil where we have taken advantage of this resource to plant a flourishing garden.

Live Oak and Santa Cruz raised the second most number of chickens in the State after Petaluma, in the heyday of egg production in the first half of the 20th century. Chanticleer Ave is named after the Chanticleer Rooster, and Live Oak was the epicenter, being the location of the local Farmer’s Exchange, an enterprise modeled after the mid west member-owned Co-ops. Two trains a day brought ingredients for chicken feed to the Exchange and they were milled and blended into feed for the members.

Live Oak is rich in history and we welcome you to explore our quiet neighborhood and discover all kinds of wonderful hidden gems.

For those of you traveling into Santa Cruz County.... our home is centrally located and close to highway one and the beach. Occasionally, there may be some freeway noise. 

My rooms are on the second floor, up stairs. My doorway requires a step up of four inches. Therefore I have to say my home is not very accessible at all. We HAVE accommodated a gentleman who just had knee surgery, and two guests with canes, who took good advantage of my staircase bannisters. 

My home is in a neighborhood with streetlights and sidewalks, and I have a very long driveway so you can park off the street.
Spring is upon us, and the days are crisp and sunny, reaching 80’s and low nineties. My home has no air conditioning, but it’s almost always a comfortable temp. The nights are in the 40's and 50's.

The beaches are very occupied, and the tourists and events are back thankfully, so our community has returned to its full and busy feel. 

We are doing our best with COVID. 
Hope to be hosting you soon. 
Peace to all and safe travels.

neighborhood_overview:
We live in the countryside area of La Selva Beach, California just south Santa Cruz over looking the picturesque and famous Monterey Bay.
It is a rural farming area with strawberry fields and miles of sandy beaches.
We are blessed with very friendly neighbors who are part of our neighborhood organizations including bi-annual community meetings, daily internet communications and even our own water company.
host_about: Carolyn and I love our Mission style home, which I built, overlooking Monterey Bay. Building the house was my retirement dream, after a 27 year career in Special Education. I was proud to create a successful program to support  18 to 22 year old autistic and other neurodivergent students. This Adult Transition Program was the first in Orange County focused on integrating these students with their peers at Orange Coast College. My staff and I helped each student, with creative job development,  individually tailored to their strengths, interests, and talents, to find work that many sustained for decades. Prior to creating this Adult Transition Program, I was the director of a school for neglected and delinquent group-home teenagers in San Francisco. Carolyn and I were college sweethearts many, many years ago, at a small Quaker College  in Indiana (Earlham). We stayed friends through marriages, raising our families, and rediscovered our love for each other after losses. Carolyn is a Psychologist and Coach, with a private practice using the Enneagram as a tool to support individuals, couples, business leaders and creatives in their growth, and the integration of head, heart and hands, to become all that they can be.  Her first career was as a Spanish Bilingual teacher in San Francisco, while Bob was working with younger students in residential treatment at ClearWater Ranch in Anderson Valley, California. We've been so happy to discover that we each maintained interests in photography, travel, hiking, snorkeling, swimming in wild waters over all the years, and are thrilled to do so together in this reignited relationship. We also enjoy playing tennis, hiking the many trails here and in Marin County, and sharing each other's friends and family. We were both psychology majors in college, where we first worked with underserved populations. We have a photo history of coast to coast adventures from the past, and we're adding more, now.
