I don't recommend walking to the beach with little ones. Like most beach neighborhoods there are no sidewalks until you get to the flat area, so if you are taking little ones to the beach I'd recommend driving. There is public parking at the beach.
host_about:
I am a happily retired Marriage and Family Therapist.   My life therefore has been about relationships that matter. 
     I am a photographer.  I love travel and color and the combination of both is  ideal for me.  
     I love hosting couples, groups of women as well as their family members. I g love their complete immersion into the pleasure of our home and its' surrounding areas.  I love my reviews when people "get it" when it comes to our  beach home.  It's fun to hear they spent time trying to imagine the stories that went behind each segment  of decor.    I LOVE France, and then Italy, and Morocco.  Canada is up there too, because they speak French (even though I don't). 
    I also fancy myself a chef (colorful, tasteful, healthy food).   Don't forget to check out all the cookbooks and international magazines.   You will know that I love cooking when you see our custom designed kitchen, the myriad of cooking utensils, french door refrigerator, Viking Stove and Bosch Dishwasher.   The french doors off the dining area open out  to extend your eating areas and invite you for morning  a cup of coffee outside.   The french doors off the living room invite you to watch the fog roll away under the palm tree.  This is yet another thing I love. 
       Walt and I have been married for 35 years.  He is still in practice as a psychologist and has taught mindfulness meditation for about 30 years.  He is the quiet type but rarely sits still.
     Interior design with elegance, color, history and a sense of whimsy would well describe another of my passions.  I like changing things up from time to time so my return guests get to do it all over again.  I love exploring our area for new things for us to do as well as always keep it fun for our guests and their children.  As nice as the house is I encourage everyone to get out there and enjoy  the outside and outlying areas as well.  Nicene Marks is almost within walking distance   The beach is a short stroll.
        I like establishing a relationship with my guests before they arrive, so I know what they need and they know what I appreciate in a guest.  People ask me, "how can you let strangers come in to this lovely home"?  Oddly, its not a problem.  To me our home is not a typical rental.  It is a shared lovely home and I think my guests understand that and feel honored to be there.  They want to maintain our relationship and so do I.
     You will get a feel for my passions as you sit on the couch in front of the fireplace, or on one of the many decks and peruse the books on design, photography, cooking and sweet novels that take place on or near the beach.
  I say to you welcome, come be an honored guest.  Wouldn't like to be my "first" Air bnb guest?

name: Home in Felton · ★4.96 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is quiet and the neighbors are lovely.  You'll meet and greet people walking the streets, enjoying the trails and shopping in downtown Felton. Felton's Farmer's market has the finest produce and flowers available; open Tuesdays starting in May; ends in October. Sushi San, Empire Grille and the Cowboy Bar & Grill are local favorites. Check out Wyler Space for unique menu offerings and even catering (check wylderspace.com for hours).  There's lots to do in and around Mt. Hermon, Henry Cowell State Park is open for walks amongst the stately Redwoods, and the Santa Cruz Boardwalk is a quick 20 minute drive down the hill.
host_about: Tim and I live in Manhattan Beach and our two daughters went to University of Wyoming.   Kim has been coming to camps at Mt. Hermon since she was in third grade, and we've continued that tradition with our family.  Tim and I enjoy North Lake Tahoe and we just went to Paris France and London with our daughters.  And yes, we stayed in VRBOs.  Loved it!  Which inspired us to try Airbnb.  We loved the homes, how well they were taken care of by the owners, and we loved living in the area versus a hotel.  Hope you like Redwood Pine House as much as we do!

host_about:
Hello! 

Welcome to my Aptos beach house. A little bit about me...

I spent 15 years living and working overseas with my family in Morocco, Lithuania, and Costa Rica. I returned to California in 2015 and fell in love with Aptos and the Monterey Bay for its beautiful beaches, mountains, and access to the San Francisco Bay Area. As a beach lover, surfer, runner, and hiker, I found Aptos to be the perfect spot to enjoy nature, the beach, and the mountains all with having quick access to San Francisco to see a Giant's baseball game or to head into Oakland or Berkeley for Ethiopian, Greek, or Indian food, to see a show, or hike in the hills. 

I love adventure travel and do most of my traveling with my kids so I understand what parents are looking for in a vacation - ease and simplicity, memory making, less time in the car and more time doing fun things together, etc.  I believe that showing children the world as often and as early as possible is important. 

“Travel is fatal to prejudice, bigotry, and narrow-mindedness, and many of our people need it sorely on these accounts. Broad, wholesome, charitable views of men and things cannot be acquired by vegetating in one little corner of the earth all one's lifetime.” - Mark Twain

I hope you enjoy my beach home and hope that you are able to explore, learn, enjoy life's simple pleasures, and make lasting memories there.
Warmly,
Sarah

Growing up surfing brought me to Santa Cruz.....and I never left. 
I won't live without clean air, pure water, art & Nature. 
A bit uncompromising yet spending a lifetime self-employed has, more or less, allowed me to live on my own terms. 
I was a retail merchant of beachwear & skateboards, transitioning into manufacture of skateboards/wheels and sponsoring the 1978 World Champion Downhill Racing Team.

The next two decades, I turned an avocation into a vocation, as a wine wholesaler. 
Then followed another decade as  a  producer and marketer of  an artisanal California extra virgin olive oil, which the LA Times twice nominated as one of the 'Top Five Calif. Olive Oils of the Year'. 
Lately I have been managing a private sports lodge in North Lake Tahoe.

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.98 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The picturesque town of Aptos is in an unincorporated area of Santa Cruz County. It is a home to historic Aptos Village, and the gateway to the Forest of Nisene Marks State Park.

Redwoods and the sea in one idyllic setting!

Rio Del Mar means “River to the Sea” in Spanish, and was coined simply as a catchy-sounding name for a new subdivision in coastal Aptos. The name has no significance beyond that. The neighborhood is popular for a number of reasons, not least of which are a number of beaches close by.

The area is known for fog, although in truth the number of foggy days is not that great, and when there is fog, it often burns off by late morning or early afternoon, leading to warm and sunny days spring through fall. Winters are normally wet, with the heaviest rainfall occurring between October and March.

The house is located in a quiet family neighborhood. You can often spot deers in the back yard and wonder at birds from the deck.

name: Condo in Capitola · ★4.83 · 1 bedroom · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Capitola is an intimate beach village tucked in a river valley in Santa Cruz County on the Monterey Bay. Located an hour away from San Jose and an hour and a half from San Francisco, Capitola enjoys a lively population full of tradition and an interesting history.
The City's wharf and riverside areas remind one of a village in France or perhaps a Mediterranean coast in Italy. Capitola Village is located along a wide beach with a breathtaking view of Monterey Bay and is home to numerous craft galleries, boutiques and restaurants. It is here where the Begonia Festival takes place each Labor Day weekend, featuring flower-draped floats and the must-see sand castle contest. Each fall the village also hosts the Annual Capitola Art & Wine Festival, which brings in over 170 artists, 10 wineries and numerous food vendors. Other visitor attractions include the Capitola Historical Museum, Capitola Wharf, and the Capitola Mall.

neighborhood_overview:
The Tuscan Country Home sits in a quiet neighborhood on two acres overlooking an orchard, pasture, and eucalyptus grove.

The home is just 10 minutes away from some of the most pristine beaches of Central Coast California. The local Seascape Resort offers patio dining and cocktails with picturesque views of the sunset. There are exceptional breweries in area and plenty of grocery stories -- all within a 10-15 minute drive.
Head 15 minutes south to Moss Landing for kayaking and whale watching, boat tours of Elkhorn Slough or continue on to Monterey Bay and Carmel.

Head north 15 minutes to Capitola where you can shop, surf and eat like a local. Stop by the wharf to pick up fresh fish or enjoy a romantic glass of wine at the Shadowbrook.

There is an abundance of wonderful things to do and see in the area! With over 40 years living in Santa Cruz, Denise has a vast knowledge of the area and can make recommendations to suit your needs.

name: Cabin in Watsonville · ★4.94 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
As as courtesy to our small, tightknit community, all neighbors are notified of guest count and arrival/departure dates. Neighbors properties have surveillance on their property and shared roads to alert them of trespassers. [Penal Code 602 PC - Trespassers will be prosecuted. The offense is a misdemeanor that carries a maximum sentence of 6 months in jail and a fine of $1000.00.]

Cabin is in the middle of a Redwood Forest surrounded by working cattle ranch with nearby and visible neighbors who take trespassing very seriously. Private road to our cabin it to only be used for accessing cabin via auto, IT IS NOT A WALKING TRAIL FOR AIRBNB GUESTS. It also can have neighbors' unfriendly dogs on it. Cows are not to be disturbed or approached.

Like any rural neighborhood, you will hear noises including dogs, roosters, chickens, ducks, chain saws, generators, blowers, tractors, trucks, distant shooting practice, visitors in travel trailers and RV's and tents etc.
host_about: My co host, Matt, and I look forward to hosting a quiet retreat for guests who can be respectful to our neighbors.  I greatly appreciate guests with strong communication and believe it is the key to making the whole Airbnb experience pleasant and smooth for everyone.  My dream is that guests will return over and over again and share the cabin with their family and friends and make memories over the years.

Santa Cruz is often valued for its location; tucked between the north and central coast of California, Santa Cruz has a mild climate, miles of sandy beaches, and a coastal redwood system that is hauntingly beautiful. But Santa Cruz offers family vacationers much more than just an ideal location, Santa Cruz is a family vacation paradise! From old fashioned carnival games to surf lessons, a Santa Cruz family vacation combines a love for modern amusements with the best of the outdoors. In Santa Cruz there is never a choice between the city and the rural life: both are essential parts of a Santa Cruz family vacation. The beautiful tide pools at Corcoran beach are just down the street, and a very short walk (less than two blocks) will take you to Sunny Cove or Santa Maria (or "Mo's", as locals know it), both great family beaches! Mo's is a great beach to take a quiet and invigorating long walk.

There is a Starbucks around the corner and there are a number of tasty restaurants within walking distance; and don't miss out on the fun local brewery. On Sundays, there is a charming little Farmer's Market only a short walk away.

The Boardwalk, the Wharf, Capitola Village and historic downtown Santa Cruz are all just a quick 10 minute drive. The Yacht Harbor and Twin Lakes Beach (with the Crow's Nest, Cafe el Palomar and Java Junction) are a three minute drive or a nice 15 minute walk away. The area is extremely bike and walking friendly, so why not enjoy the area without dealing with the stresses of traffic!!!

I am a professional Airbnb host and a former elementary school teacher and Katharina is an amazing person and an incredibly talented creative director. Oliver is a bright, energetic and friendly young man that loves the water, bike riding, history, exploring and solving the mysteries of the universe. We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.94 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The lower Westside of Santa Cruz is a quiet, family-friendly haven that's still close to all the action. It's just a 5-minute walk to Natural Bridges Beach and State Park, which is known for its wildlife, including shore birds, migratory whales, seals and otters. Not to mention the Monarch Butterfly Sanctuary at the Park—visit in late October and into November to observe peak monarch migration.

For a bit more activity, you're also just a 10-minute drive to the Beach Boardwalk and within walking distance of Santa Cruz's thriving and creative brewery and winery district. The Seymour Marine Discovery Center—a community-supported marine science education center affiliated with UC-Santa Cruz—is also nearby.

Kendall & Potter was established as a real estate company over fifty years ago. 
The brokers Skipper Kendall and William Potter moved to Aptos to fulfill their dream of working in a small town in Santa Cruz County. They soon expanded their services to include property management and relocation to Santa Cruz County along the Monterey Coast.

Kendall & Potter continues to be seen as one of the leading forces in Santa Cruz County Real Estate Property Management.

Rita Law, now owner and broker, purchased the property department and has been on site for nearly 50 years.

Kendall & Potter Property Management offers a variety of home services – including complete property management services, leases on unfurnished properties and rental homes in Santa Cruz, as well as Monterey Coast & Santa Cruz vacation rentals management and corporate housing.

Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. name: Home in Aptos · ★4.88 · 3 bedrooms · 5 beds · 2.5 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Aptos is a coastal gem nestled in Santa Cruz County. With its stunning beaches, including Rio del Mar and Seacliff State Beach, it's a haven for sun-seekers and surf enthusiasts. This charming town boasts a laid-back vibe, a mix of boutique shops, and a vibrant dining scene, making it a perfect destination for a relaxing vacation. The iconic Cement Ship at Seacliff Beach is a must-see, and nearby forested parks like Nisene Marks offer hiking and biking trails. Aptos combines natural beauty, small-town charm, and easy access to the Santa Cruz Boardwalk, creating an ideal coastal escape for visitors.

This is a very quiet, family neighborhood. It is not a good place for gatherings or parties so please keep that in mind when booking this home. We are very respectful of our neighbors and will not tolerate loud noise past curfew and additional guests at the property.

name: Cottage in Santa Cruz · ★4.94 · 2 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The Beach Cottage Near Sunny Cove and Santa Mo's is in a fantastic and central location. The beautiful tide pools at Corcoran beach are steps away and a very short walk (less than two blocks) will take you to Sunny Cove or Santa Maria (or "Mo's", as locals know it), both great family beaches! Mo's is a great beach to take a quiet and invigorating long walk.

There is a Starbucks around the corner and there are a number of tasty restaurants within walking distance; and don't miss out on the fun local brewery nearby! On Sundays there is a charming little Farmer's Market, also a short walk away.

The Boardwalk, the Wharf, Capitola Village and historic downtown Santa Cruz are all just a quick 10 minute drive (or less then 20 minute bike ride). The Yacht Harbor and Twin Lakes Beach (with the Crow's Nest, Cafe el Palomar and Java Junction) are a three minute drive or a nice 15 minute walk away. The area is extremely bike and walking friendly, so why not enjoy the area w

I live in Santa Cruz, California with my wonderful wife Katharina and our son Oliver. I am a professional Airbnb host and a former elementary school teacher and Katharina is an amazing person and an incredibly talented creative director. Oliver is a bright, energetic and friendly young man that loves the water, bike riding, history, exploring and solving the mysteries of the universe. We have one incredibly friendly and mellow cat (Dexter), six chickens and we enjoy spending time with friends--hiking, biking, great home-cooked meals, good wine and beer, and generally enjoying all that life has to offer.

We have a passion for travel--nothing is more exciting then finding yourself in a new and unfamiliar place with nothing to do but explore and interact with new people!

We are also extremely responsible people. We own our home and take great pride in having a place that is clean, comfortable and inviting. As guests in other people's homes, we feel the same responsibility and respect for their space.

Pleasure Point is a beloved coastal neighborhood. Known for its world-class surfing, laid-back ambiance, and breathtaking ocean views, it's a haven for beachgoers and water enthusiasts. The iconic surf breaks like "The Hook" attract surfers from around the world. This vibrant community boasts a unique blend of surf shops, cafes, and local boutiques. Stroll along East Cliff Drive, savor fresh seafood, or catch a mesmerizing sunset from the cliffs. With its bohemian spirit and proximity to the lively Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, Pleasure Point offers a quintessential California beach experience.

name: Place to stay in Watsonville · ★4.91 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our listing is located on just over 4 acres in a redwood forest up a canyon. Our location has a park-like setting. Our guests will have private use of the camp area, which is situated in a separate location on the property, but it is in close proximity to our home residence. Our closest neighbor is a Buddhist Retreat Center, which for the most part, is a quiet sanctuary. However, they do occasionally host weddings and if you are visiting on one of those weekends, you can expect to hear some noise/music from the reception, which always ends promptly at 10pm. Guests can also expect to hear some occasional road noise.
Because we are located in a wilderness area, we co-exist with wild life critters. They are around, but not often seen. The wild animals that live in our area include owls, hawks and other birds, foxes, coyotes, raccoons, skunks, squirrels, deer, bobcats and mountain lions.
host_about: We are a family of four. Ismael is a teacher who runs a local nonprofit outdoor education program for underserved youth (Growing Up Wild). Molly is a registered nurse. We have two fun loving boys. Our home, where the glamping retreat is located, is a private campground in the redwood forest. It is a beautiful and serene forest setting with a running creek and lots of wildlife.

name: Guest suite in Santa Cruz · ★4.95 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The guest suite is special because of its remote feel of the woods, despite its close proximity to Santa Cruz's beautiful beaches. It is located at the end of a cul-de-sac in a residential neighborhood. Main Beach and The Boardwalk are 3.3 miles away, with tasty restaurants and cute shops even closer on Pacific Avenue.

Head north 15 minutes to Capitola where you can shop, surf and eat like a local. Stop by the wharf to pick up fresh fish or enjoy a romantic glass of wine at the Shadowbrook.

The Santa Cruz Mountains offer a serene escape from the hustle and bustle. neighborhood_overview:
The Tuscan Tin Can is just 10 minutes away from some of the most pristine beaches of Central Coast California.

The local Seascape Resort offers patio dining and cocktails with picturesque views of the sunset. There are exceptional breweries in area and plenty of grocery stories -- all within a 10-15 minute drive.
Head 15 minutes south to Moss Landing for kayaking and whale watching, boat tours of Elkhorn Slough or continue on to Monterey Bay and Carmel.

Head north 15 minutes to Capitola where you can shop, surf and eat like a local. Stop by the wharf to pick up fresh fish or enjoy a romantic glass of wine at the Shadowbrook.

There is an abundance of wonderful things to do and see in the area! With over 40 years living in Santa Cruz, Denise has a vast knowledge of the area and can make recommendations to suit your needs.

My Italian heritage is at the heart of my approach to hospitality and design. From colour and texture to rustic design details, local wines and the pizza rolls that greet guests upon their arrival, the Italian influence is clear. 

When it comes to hosting, I pride myself on providing a warm and welcoming environment for each and every guest. With quality at the heart of my philosophy, I go above and beyond to ensure that all of my guests have a remarkable stay.

At Natural Bridges State Beach, gorgeous sandy shores and creature-filled tidepools lure beachgoers while a lush eucalyptus grove draws thousands of migrating Monarch butterflies each fall and winter. Leading to and from Natural Bridges is stunning West Cliff Drive, a multi-use, waterfront trail that teems with joggers, cyclists, and pedestrians basking in the glory of the Monterey Bay. Go at sundown for the real show! The historic dairy grounds of Wilder Ranch State Park features miles of singletrack trails for mountain bikers as well as the outrageously scenic Old Cove Landing Trail which ambles along dramatic coastal bluffs. The beautiful Natural Bridges Farm invites visitors to wander its bloom-filled grounds and fill a basket with fresh veggies, fruits, and flowers plucked directly from the soil.

Kendall & Potter was established as a real estate company over fifty years ago.

name: Home in Aptos · ★4.96 · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 3 baths

neighborhood_overview: We are located 1.5 blocks from the famed Santa Cruz Boardwalk, beach, wharf and some of the best surfing in the world on West Cliff drive. So much to see and do just steps away.
host_about:
Hi there! 

I'm Dominique.  I have always loved living near the water and spent much of my childhood living on a houseboat in Key West, Florida. (Pretty sure I have seawater running through my veins.) I have lived in several places before making Santa Cruz my permanent home, including; Mexico, NYC, New Orleans (I tend to only live in places Jimmy Buffet sings about. ; ) ) 

My day job for the past 25 years has been teaching and owning a Pilates studio and my husband Erik is an "almost" retired (can't get him to actually leave) Fireman/Paramedic. 

We love to travel and have stayed in Airbnbs all over the world. We get what makes a "home away from home" great and how much the place you stay can impact your experience of a location. 

We are excited to share our Santa Cruz home with you. We raised our daughter here for the first 10 years of her life so far... enjoying the beach, Boardwalk, wharf and walks along West Cliff.  We have spent so many happy memories here and we're convinced you and your family and friends will too!

name: Loft in Bonny Doon · ★4.94 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
We are in the mountains surrounded by redwoods, meadows and a winery. 1 mile up the road is an ecological preserve with great hiking. It is 3 miles down the mountain to a nice beach. The roads around us don't have a lot of cars so the area is great for bicycling. Go north on Highway One and you are at Davenport, an old whaling town with a nice restaurant and another nice beach. Just further north on the coast is Ano Nuevo State Park, where the giant elephant seals raise their babies on the beach each spring. Also close by are Big Basin State Park (unfortunately shut down temporarily after the fires), Wilder Ranch State Park, Henry Cowell State Park and many other great parks.

And of course, we are only 13 miles north of the wonderful town of Santa Cruz.

The apartment sits in the middle of a compound that includes a large garden, fruit orchard and 2 other guest units, protected by a deer fence. You can access our own pond which thru a pathway down the hill
host_about:
My day job is investing in technology, hosting startup events and I do some consulting.  But my wife and I also have this magical place in the Santa Cruz mountains, in a clearing amongst the redwoods, next to a great winery, and only 3 miles from the beach.   We have our own pond, and we have surrounded ourselves with fruit trees and floral gardens, which we hope you will enjoy.  When we are not around, our caretaker, Ed Olson, takes care of our guests.  

We hope to create a Shangri-la feel for our guests - totally relaxed in the mountains and nature, but with all the comforts of home.  We are also frequent travelers, so we know how important it is to feel at home when staying in new accomodations.

host_about:
My name is Jessica I am a single mom of an amazing 5 year old little boy. Yeah I tend to lead my intro about my son because he is a big part of who I am and well because he is awesome…haha! And because he makes me a better person, I wouldn’t be who I am without him. 
Anyway- I’m Jessica, I from Santa Cruz California. I work in the medical industry and love the outdoors, meeting new people, and trying new things. Some of my favorite places to travel are; Germany, Italy, Hawaii and Canada as well the US States.  My partner in crime (not real crime obviously) if my son is not with me is my other half Stephen (an Environmental Geologist). We love to travel as a couple and as a family. We are all very clean and I am a firm believer in treating others and their things the way you want to be treated, that’s what I like to model and teach my son. 
In short we are a fun loving, hardworking group that want to travel and teach my son the amazing learning experiences traveling has to offer.

name: Rental unit in Santa Cruz · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
This is in a dream location! At the edge of the neighborhood, you can hike the Redwoods via "The Enchanted Trail" or other hikes from De La Viega Park trailheads just a walk from your front door. 3 famous beaches are within 2.5 miles, and also UC Santa Cruz. You can drive 6 miles to renowned Henry Cowell State Park or 7 miles to the Forest of Nicene Marks State Park.

There's charm galore, w/ downtown Santa Cruz restaurants & shops along Pacific Ave an easy bike ride away (1.5 miles, and we have bikes for you), plus darling neighboring towns - Capitola, Aptos & Soquel.

Enjoy hot tub soaks under the stars or Backyard BBQ (by appointment, available most nights).

Though u feel like you're in a faraway beach paradise, you can also get to the heart of Silicon Valley (Apple, LinkedIn, Googl & Facebk HQs are 35-40 mins away--and employee shuttles pick-up right near) and San Jose airport is just a 33 min drive. Day trips to San Francisco are also easily access
host_about:
Hi, We're Christy and Barry...We are Adventurers who have been jazzed to be Airbnb Guests for over a decade. Our most priceless Airbnb memories are when we unplugged from our Silicon Valley life with our 2 kids and traveled around the world together for half a year, living and volunteering in Orphanages in rural villages in India, Thailand, Kenya, Uganda and Honduras. As we traveled between those countries, we stayed in Airbnb homes in between (Spain, Italy, Athens, Amsterdam, Iceland, and more).  We were warmly welcomed at every stay. 
We just became empty nesters with our kids away to college/Post-college, so we bought a home in one of our favorite places on earth -- Santa Cruz, where breathtaking Redwoods meet the shore in a charming beach community. We are so excited to live in Santa Cruz now and explore all its beautiful treasures, Learn the rich history, and enjoy this inclusive, thoughtful community.  

We were taken by this home when we saw the For Sale sign on an Anniversary sSanta Cruz visit. The owner Ted wanted to create a little tropical paradise and it was so clear that she had done so as an absolute labor of love. (You’ll see the hand carved doors from Bali and other authentic tropical touches). We moved into the home as soon as we could and we now spend alternate weekends caring for my aging mom in our former town, so when we are able, we love being able to provide magical, memorable Guest experiences for Guests, just as our Hosts have done for us around the world. <3

name: Bungalow in Santa Cruz · ★4.83 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Twin Lakes has become a well-loved beach by locals and tourists, and Woods Lagoon now harbors hundreds of fishing and pleasure boats. The slightly warmer water (compared to Seabright) and sandy seafloor make for some great bodysurfing here, and the freshwater that flows onto the beach from Schwan Lake is a sandcastle architect’s dream. Towards the harbor end of the beach, athletic types can challenge each other to a game of beach volleyball, while the not-so-sporty among us can watch from one of several ocean view restaurants. If you’re on vacation (or not), go ahead and eat your way through the day here: start the morning with coffee or cocktails directly nextdoor at The Harbor Cafe, fuel up on Mexican fare at Cafe El Palomar for lunch, and after a long day in the sun, enjoy dinner and drinks at The Crow’s Nest on the upper deck overlooking the harbor channel.

Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

This is not a good place for gatherings or parties so please keep that in mind when booking this home. We are very respectful of our neighbors and will not tolerate loud noise past curfew and additional guests at the property.

name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★4.97 · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 3.5 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Pleasure Point in Santa Cruz is a captivating coastal destination that embodies the essence of California beach culture. Located along the scenic Monterey Bay, this vibrant neighborhood offers a unique blend of natural beauty and laid-back charm.

Pleasure Point is renowned for its world-class surf breaks, attracting surfers from all over the globe. Watch in awe as skilled riders carve through the waves, showcasing their talent and creating an exhilarating spectacle. The rhythmic crashing of the surf and the salty ocean breeze create a mesmerizing atmosphere that embodies the spirit of the ocean.

Beyond its renowned surf spots, Pleasure Point offers breathtaking coastal views and picturesque landscapes. Take a leisurely stroll along East Cliff Drive, where you can admire the stunning vistas of the Pacific Ocean and take in the sights and sounds of this coastal paradise. The coastal path is perfect for biking, jogging, or simply enjoying a peaceful sunset walk.

We have two little ones that light up our life and we want to show them the world.

We've been helping people make terrific Santa Cruz Memories for generations.  Let us assist in making your next beach vacation amazing.

Kendall & Potter was established as a real estate company over fifty years ago. 
The brokers Skipper Kendall and William Potter moved to Aptos to fulfill their dream of working in a small town in Santa Cruz County. They soon expanded their services to include property management and relocation to Santa Cruz County along the Monterey Coast.

Kendall & Potter continues to be seen as one of the leading forces in Santa Cruz County Real Estate Property Management.

Rita Law, now owner and broker, purchased the property department and has been on site for nearly 50 years.

Kendall & Potter Property Management offers a variety of home services – including complete property management services, leases on unfurnished properties and rental homes in Santa Cruz, as well as Monterey Coast & Santa Cruz vacation rentals management and corporate housing.

name: Home in Capitola · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2.5 baths
host_about:
Sanctuary Vacation Rentals represents properties throughout Carmel, Pebble Beach, Pacific Grove, Carmel Highlands, and the Big Sur coastline. We combine fine resort accommodations and relaxed elegance with all the comforts of home. 
Our properties are places that nurture and inspire and are located in one of the most beautiful, energizing places in the world, featuring the spectacular scenery of the Monterey Peninsula and the central coast of California.  From historic old Monterey, to the Victorian charm of Pacific Grove, and the artists colony of Carmel-by-the-Sea, and the breathtaking scenery of Big Sur, generations of people have been rejuvenated by the breaking waves and sandy beaches here.
Our properties are designer furnished with relaxed elegance.  Many homes feature the colors of the sea and take inspiration from the natural beauty of the surrounding areas.
Throughout Sanctuary’s vacation rentals, you’ll find comfortable beds with luxury linens, welcome beverages and hors d’oeuvres, spa robes and amenities, local wine tasting and spa passes, and a personal concierge to assist you in every way.  Our homes feature chef’s dream kitchens and everything you’ll need to entertain in style.  And many of our properties are pet friendly.
If you’re looking for a refreshing, relaxed stay in one of the most beautiful areas in the world– offering all the comforts of home, let Sanctuary Vacation Rentals help you discover your own sanctuary by the sea.  

The Monterey Peninsula is unique in its combination of breathtaking natural resources and a multiplicity of cultural and entertainment possibilities. You can find something for every possible taste. For nature lovers, there is the diversity of mountain and sea, for picnicking, surfing, fishing, horseback riding, hiking, beach-combing, bird-watching, kayaking, scuba diving, tide-pooling, biking and more. If you want a man-made excitement, we have art galleries galore, excellent fine-art museums, local theatre, outstanding restaurants, boutiques, a natural history and a children's museum, a world-class aquarium, and that's just for starters. History buffs will have a field day exploring the adobes of Monterey. There's so much to do that you cannot possibly do it all in one visit, which means you will have to come back.

Rita Law, now owner and broker, purchased the property department and has been on site for nearly 50 years.

host_about:
My name is Dan O’Bannon and I have been a self employed Cabinet Maker for the past 33 years and  have been working with  my right hand Man, my Son Matt, for the past 10 years.   I enjoy nature and animals.  My Cat, Will Feral, was a wild stray that I took in,  he keeps me entertained.  I enjoy watching and attending Baseball games,  watching movies,  listening to music, and spending time with family and friends.  I have done some background acting (although not lately) in a few movies and TV shows  over the past 15 years and had a lot of fun playing a Barbosa Pirate in the first  "Pirates of the Caribbean" movie with my Son and Brother.  I've also enjoyed singing and playing the guitar with my Son Matt and my Brothers in the past.  
I moved to Santa Cruz in 1970 and have lived at my Country Home in Watsonville for the past 20 years.  Keeping up three acres, running my business and spending time with family & friends keeps me busy!   I have a very full life and I am grateful!

neighborhood_overview: Bonny Doon is a special place. It hosts a variety of micro climates and vistas. From the majestic redwood forest to chaparrals, to manzanita and madrone forests it is truly a magical place. We hope our guests take some time to explore the ecological reserve (3 minute drive from our place), the great and famous giant redwood, ‘Big Ben, just up the street from us, the hundreds of world class biking trails that can be accessed along the beautiful Empire Grade Road. The new state park, part of the Coast Diaries and so much more! Our property sits at about 2000 feet elevation, sometimes in the winter months we get a beautiful dusting of snow. It’s south facing and on clear days if you hike up the property there is a little window view of the Pacific Ocean. The fresh pacific morning fog will sometimes come in but mostly in the summer months we are greeted by the warm sun. The Laguna creek passes through our neighborhood and our property creating yet another micro environment of ferns, moss,

neighborhood_overview:
West Cliff Drive is a scenic, 3-mile walking and biking path along the Pacific Ocean in Santa Cruz with epic views of the Monterey Bay.

Beginning at the Santa Cruz Municipal Wharf, West Cliff Drive takes you past the Santa Cruz Dream Inn, West Cliff Inn, Sea & Sand, and the Seaway Inn toward a residential neighborhood. It is here you will find locals mixing effortlessly with visitors strolling, biking, running, walking their dogs, and pushing babies in strollers as surfers head toward Steamer Lane for the surf break.

Walk to the surfer statue – one of the best places to snap a selfie – and take in the views of the wharf, boardwalk, and mellow surfers at Cowell Beach. As you head north, you’ll pass by Cypress Trees found along West Cliff Drive, iconic to the Central Coast. name: Home in Santa Cruz · ★New · 4 bedrooms · 5 beds · 3.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: Santa Cruz, California, is a coastal town with a unique blend of natural beauty and vibrant culture. Known for its stunning beaches along West Cliff Drive, it's a paradise for sunbathers, surfers, and outdoor enthusiasts. The Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk offers classic seaside fun with thrilling rides and amusements. The town's lively downtown area is dotted with eclectic shops, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Santa Cruz is also a hub for live music and cultural events, with the Santa Cruz Wharf offering spectacular ocean views and fresh seafood. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventures or relaxation, Santa Cruz has it all, making it a dynamic and inviting coastal destination.

host_about:
I am a retired nurse who specialized in labor and delivery, and post partum care. For over forty years I have taught childbirth classes and parenting classes in both English and Spanish. For a number of years when my daughter was young, I was a co-director of a co-op pre-school.  I founded and was director of a Family Resource Center for 10 years, and then took a great sabbatical that was full of traveling,  hiking the John Muir Trail, and climbing Mt. Whitney and Mt. Rainer. For a number of years I did hospice nursing, and now I have retired from nursing and I am spending a lot of time with my grandson and his parents in Florida.  
My dad was a rower at Cal in 1939, and my 100 year old aunt just rowed a 2000 meter in 19:27. The book The Boys in the Boat is a really fun read.
